{
  "article_id": "EnglewoodTimes1905",
  "paragraphs": [
    [
      {
        "text": "Beginning due west of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Point Conception",
        "entity_key": "re_pc",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "on the"
      },
      {
        "text": "California",
        "entity_key": "st_cal",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "coast and continuing at irregular intervals as far south as "
      },
      {
        "text": "the bay of Todos",
        "entity_key": "re_todosbay",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "Santos, in "
      },
      {
        "text": "Lower California",
        "entity_key": "re_baja",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "lie "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Channel Islands",
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". In this ideal region for the yachtman, the fisherman and the hunter, one comes to feel like a new "
      },
      {
        "text": "Crusoe",
        "entity_key": "rcr",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "on "
      },
      {
        "text": "his primitive isle",
        "entity_key": "i_jf",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". "
      },
      {
        "text": "And in very truth Crusoe's semi-mythical story was enacted upon ",
        "tropes": [
          8,
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "one of these same islands",
        "tropes": [
          8,
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", though minus the man Friday and the happy ending.",
        "tropes": [
          8,
          3
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The castaway",
        "tropes": [
          3,
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "in this case was a woman, a Danish imigrant, left ashore through some mischance by the crew of a vessel that had sought shelter behind ",
        "tropes": [
          3,
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicholas",
        "tropes": [
          3,
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "during a storm in the early [18]'50's. For over seventeen years ",
        "tropes": [
          3,
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the lone creature",
        "tropes": [
          3,
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "lived unsought and forgotten, though the time at length came when, on the days the mist-clearing north wind blew, she could climb to the island's highest point and view the ranchers' herds grazing upon the mainland.",
        "tropes": [
          3,
          8
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "And at last, when hope and reason had both long died, ",
        "tropes": [
          14
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the poor, wild, gibbering creature",
        "tropes": [
          14
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "was found in her wolf's burrow among the hills by ",
        "tropes": [
          14
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the advance guard of the otter hunters' fraternity",
        "tropes": [
          14
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "gni",
          "cdi",
          "col",
          "cook",
          "msh",
          "poli",
          "nsk",
          "hva"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who had long wondered at the mysterious footprints they marked upon the lonely sands.",
        "tropes": [
          14
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "—"
      }
    ]
  ]
}